In this task, I explored both coding and collaboration platforms to understand their practical use in academics. I used HackerRank to complete a beginner-level coding challenge, which helped me improve my logical thinking and problem-solving skills. It also gave me an introduction to how coding platforms are used for practice and skill development.
For the collaboration part, I created a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz using Google Forms. The quiz included different types of questions such as multiple-choice and short answers. I also observed the responses in Google Sheets, which showed how data can be collected and analyzed easily.
Overall, this task helped me understand the importance of using online tools for learning, practicing coding, and collaborating efficiently in academic work.
